SECTION 2: RAWCRAFT ADJUDICATION

Any character may bite and chew any ingredient to experience a weak, brief version of its
primary Essence. The GM narrates the effect:

  VITALIS:    A brief warmth; the player's minor surface wounds close slightly.
              They feel momentarily invigorated.
  VENITAS:    Nausea, mild disorientation, or localized pain depending on the source.
              Brief and survivable. The character grimaces.
  GRAVITAS:   A heaviness in the limbs, lasting 10-15 seconds real time. Their step
              is briefly sluggish.
  AGILITAS:   A brief improvement in reaction time. The character might catch something
              they would have dropped.
  CAECITAS:   Colors dim slightly. Ambient noise muffles briefly. Lasts seconds.
  FORTITAS:   A brief sensation of solidity — the character feels, for a moment, like
              their skin has become more substantial.
  ANIMA:      Variable. Roll a d4 and describe accordingly:
              1 — Mild euphoria. 2 — Heightened awareness.
              3 — A strange sense of doubled perception. 4 — Nothing visible;
              the character simply feels that something happened.
  IGNIS:      A localized warmth at the point of contact. Often pleasant in small amounts.
  GLACIES:    A localized chill; brief numbness at the lips/mouth.
  FULGUR:     A mild tingling at the point of contact.

RAWCRAFT RISK: If the ingredient's primary Essence is VENITAS or has a dangerous elemental
primary (IGNIS from Fire Salts, for instance), the character experiences a mild but real
effect. It is survivable. It is not comfortable. If a player Rawcrafts something truly
dangerous without any knowledge of what it is, feel free to apply 1 HP damage and describe
it vividly. This is how early alchemists died. Make it feel like that.

WHAT RAWCRAFT REVEALS (GATED BY KNOWLEDGE, NOT RANK)
  Alchemy is gated by what a character KNOWS, never by a skill rank. The tongue does not
  improve with tier; the knowing does. In the tasting, a character reads the Essences
  they have the knowledge to recognize:
    Knows little of the essences:  the loudest (Primary) only.
    Has studied the essences:      two at once.
    Knows the essences cold:       every Essence the thing carries.
  Adjudicate by what the character has actually learned -- study, a reference like the
  Doctrine or the Codex, a teacher, prior use of that ingredient -- not by a number on a
  sheet. A beginner feels only the loudest essence not because a seal is closed to them,
  but because they have not yet learned to recognize the rest of what they already feel.


