COMMON INGREDIENTS (FOUND IN SKYRIM WILDERNESS)

Blue Mountain Flower
  VITALIS [P]
  CAECITAS [S]    (resist magic property in Skyrim maps to concealment of self)
  Use: Primary healing source. Foundational recipe ingredient.

Wheat
  VITALIS [P]
  FORTITAS [S]   (fortify health maps to physical hardening/resilience)
  Use: Most common VITALIS secondary. Combines with Blue Mountain Flower
  for the basic healing potion. Clean: no opposition interactions.

Blisterwort
  VITALIS [P]
  FORTITAS [S]
  Use: Alternative to Wheat in healing compounds. Stronger VITALIS expression.

Imp Stool
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  VITALIS [S]    (restore health — secondary, creates design tension)
  GRAVITAS [T]   (ravage speed in Skyrim)
  GM NOTE: This ingredient is a perfect teaching tool for the Opposition system.
  A player combining Imp Stool with Blue Mountain Flower has VENITAS[P] vs VITALIS[P]
  — PRIMARY NEGATION. The brew collapses. A Novice who doesn't know the secondaries
  yet might not realize this is coming.

Deathbell
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  GRAVITAS [S]   (slow)
  Use: Primary poison base. Common in poisoner kits.

Skeever Tail
  VENITAS [P]    (damage health)
  AGILITAS [T]   (ravage skill, loosening of control — marginal)
  Use: Basic poison source. Easy to obtain.

Mora Tapinella
  VENITAS [S]    (damage health secondary)
  ANIMA [P]      (restore magicka — spirit/mind adjacent; also hallucination properties)
  AGILITAS [T]   (regenerate stamina)
  GM NOTE: The ANIMA/VENITAS pairing here is NOT an opposition pair.
  ANIMA opposes FORTITAS, not VENITAS. These two express independently.

Thistle Branch
  GRAVITAS [P]   (resist frost maps to anchoring/hardening against cold — but note:
                  frost resist in our system is FORTITAS+GLACIES, so this is better
                  mapped as GRAVITAS since Thistle also has Slow effect)
  FORTITAS [S]   (resist frost: physical hardening against elemental)
  GM NOTE: Thistle Branch is a dual-purpose ingredient. Use your judgment on which
  property the player is targeting. If they describe wanting to slow someone, the
  GRAVITAS is primary. If they describe cold resistance, frame FORTITAS as the
  expressed Essence with GLACIES implied.

Swamp Fungal Pod
  AGILITAS [P]   (paralysis — note: paralysis is AGILITAS at extreme high concentration
                  overwhelming the nervous system, the opposite of its healing expression;
                  functionally it is AGILITAS applied adversely)
  CAECITAS [S]   (resist shock — concealment from electrical force maps here loosely)
  GM NOTE: AGILITAS at very high concentration can paradoxically produce paralysis --
  the flooding of the speed-channels overwhelms the nervous system. Treat this as a
  recognized edge case of the craft; it is also how Paralysis Poison is built (Section 9).

Canis Root
  AGILITAS [P]   (fortify one-handed, paralysis — speed and precision)
  GRAVITAS [S]   (damage stamina — weight on the system)
  GM NOTE: Canis Root has an internal AGILITAS[P]/GRAVITAS[S] tension.
  This is SECONDARY NEGATION — both Essences are present but the AGILITAS
  dominates. The GRAVITAS is significantly weakened. The compound skews speed
  but with some drag on the system.

Juniper Berries
  AGILITAS [P]   (fortify marksman — speed and precision of shot)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage stamina regen — entropy on the stamina system)
  Use: Speed-adjacent. The VENITAS[S] is not opposed to AGILITAS (GRAVITAS opposes it),
  so both express. A brewer using Juniper Berries gets speed effects with a mild
  stamina-drain secondary.

Luna Moth Wing
  CAECITAS [P]   (invisibility)
  FORTITAS [S]   (fortify one-handed — physical empowerment)
  Use: Primary invisibility source. Clean CAECITAS carrier.

Nirnroot
  CAECITAS [P]   (damage health — adverse concealment: used to dull/blind the body)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage stamina)
  FULGUR [T]     (the luminous glow and magical resonance map to FULGUR)
  GM NOTE: Nirnroot's CAECITAS[P] vs FULGUR[T] — TERTIARY NEGATION only.
  The glow barely affects the concealment property. This is the ingredient's
  famous magical paradox: it glows (FULGUR) but its dominant property is
  concealment/dulling (CAECITAS). Slight weakening on both, negligible in play.

Chaurus Eggs
  FULGUR [P]     (resist shock)
  CAECITAS [S]   (invisibility)
  FORTITAS [T]   (fortify stamina — physical hardening)
  GM NOTE: CAECITAS[S] vs FULGUR[P] — SECONDARY NEGATION on the CAECITAS.
  The invisibility property of Chaurus Eggs is significantly weakened.
  This is canon-accurate: Chaurus Eggs are primarily used for shock effects,
  not invisibility.

Vampire Dust
  ANIMA [P]      (soul trap, invisibility — spirit energy and concealment)
  CAECITAS [S]   (invisibility secondary)
  VITALIS [T]    (restore magicka — the life-adjacent energy)
  GM NOTE: ANIMA[P] and CAECITAS[S] do not oppose each other (ANIMA opposes FORTITAS,
  CAECITAS opposes FULGUR). Both express. The VITALIS[T] is also non-opposing.
  A full three-Essence expression. Complex but stable ingredient.

Luna Moth Wing and Vampire Dust together:
  Both carry CAECITAS — Affinity applies, CAECITAS amplified.
  ANIMA from Vampire Dust adds a spirit-adjacent secondary.
  Result: Strong concealment potion with a minor ANIMA note — the invisibility
  has a spiritual quality, harder for magical detection to pierce.

Nordic Barnacle
  FORTITAS [P]   (resist poison — physical hardening against toxins)
  VITALIS [S]    (restore health)
  Use: Clean FORTITAS primary with healing secondary. Good resistance base.

Scaly Pholiota
  FORTITAS [P]   (fortify stamina — the body hardened to endure more)
  AGILITAS [S]   (fortify two-handed — speed and force of movement)
  Use: Fortify/speed combination. FORTITAS and AGILITAS do not oppose each other.
  Both express fully.

Giant's Toe
  ANIMA [P]      (fortify health, fortify carry weight — spirit/body boundary pushing)
  FORTITAS [S]   (fortify stamina)
  VITALIS [T]    (restore health)
  GM NOTE: ANIMA[P] and FORTITAS[S] — SECONDARY NEGATION (FORTITAS opposes ANIMA).
  The FORTITAS stamina effect is significantly weakened. The ANIMA effect dominates.
  Giant's Toe is famously powerful and famously weird in its interactions.

Human Heart
  ANIMA [P]      (damage magicka, frenzy — deep spirit disruption)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage health)
  FORTITAS [T]   (fortify magicka — body-spirit interface)
  GM NOTE: ANIMA[P] and FORTITAS[T] — TERTIARY NEGATION. Barely matters.
  The VENITAS[S] does not oppose ANIMA. Both express.
  This is one of the most ethically complex ingredients in the catalogue.
  See Section 6 on sapient ingredients.

Fire Salts
  IGNIS [P]      (fire damage)
  FORTITAS [S]   (resist fire — when paired with FORTITAS, creates fire resistance)
  GM NOTE: Fire Salts with a FORTITAS carrier = fire resistance potion.
  Fire Salts alone = fire damage compound (adverse application).
  IGNIS[P] and FORTITAS[S] do not oppose each other. The Retort determines
  which Essence dominates in the expression — the brewer's intent and technique.

Frost Salts
  GLACIES [P]    (frost damage)
  FORTITAS [S]   (resist frost)
  ANIMA [T]      (slow — cold slowing the spirit's influence on the body)
  Use: Mirrors Fire Salts. Frost damage primary; frost resistance when combined
  with additional FORTITAS source.

Void Salts
  FULGUR [P]     (shock damage)
  CAECITAS [S]   (resist shock — concealment from electrical disruption)
  VENITAS [T]    (damage health — entropy secondary from shock)
  GM NOTE: FULGUR[P] vs CAECITAS[S] — SECONDARY NEGATION. The shock resistance
  property is significantly weakened when Void Salts are the primary ingredient.
  This is consistent with Skyrim canon where Void Salts' shock resist is a weaker
  property than its shock damage.

Snowberries
  GLACIES [S]    (resist frost — cold is secondary, not primary)
  FORTITAS [P]   (resist fire, resist shock — physical hardening is primary)
  FULGUR [T]     (resist shock — shock resistance maps loosely to FULGUR)
  GM NOTE: GLACIES[S] and FORTITAS[P] — no opposition (they are not an opposing pair).
  Both express. FULGUR[T] and GLACIES[S] are also not an opposing pair.
  Snowberries are one of the cleanest multi-Essence resistance ingredients in the catalogue.

Slaughterfish Egg
  FORTITAS [P]   (resist frost)
  VENITAS [S]    (damage health)
  Use: Fortify/resist primary. VENITAS[S] adds an entropic secondary that a skilled
  brewer should account for.

River Betty
  GRAVITAS [P]   (slow, damage health — weighing down the target)
  FORTITAS [S]   (resist frost — physical hardening)
  Use: Slowing compound primary. Good GRAVITAS source.

Cyrodilic Spadetail
  GRAVITAS [P]   (damage stamina — weighing down endurance)
  AGILITAS [S]   (restore stamina — speed of recovery)
  GM NOTE: GRAVITAS[P] vs AGILITAS[S] — SECONDARY NEGATION. Both effects
  significantly weakened when combined in the same ingredient. This ingredient
  is internally conflicted. Its most reliable use is as a secondary GRAVITAS
  source in a brew where something else carries GRAVITAS as primary.

Ashen Grass Pod
  IGNIS [S]      (resist fire — fire-adjacent but not primary fire expression)
  FORTITAS [P]   (fortify stamina — physical endurance primary)
  Use: Good FORTITAS source with a mild fire-resistance secondary.

Flame Stalk
  IGNIS [P]      (fire damage)
  AGILITAS [S]   (fortify stamina — fire's association with speed and energy)
  Use: Direct fire damage source. The AGILITAS secondary adds speed/energy to
  fire compounds — a "burning with energy" compound could combine these.

Stalhrim (trace material in potions)
  FULGUR [P]     (resist shock — the crystalline structure channels electrical force)
  GLACIES [S]    (frost damage — cold crystalline nature)
  GM NOTE: Rare ingredient. FULGUR[P] and GLACIES[S] are not an opposing pair.
