SECTION 10: THE FORELHOST STRAIN (THE SCOURGE)

The Forelhost line's signature work, and the disease at the center of the Dragon Cult
plague arc. The in-world account is in the Forelhost Codex (Lore Books); this is the
mechanical adjudication.

WHAT IT IS
  An engineered VENITAS disease bound with the Tears of Rahgot so that it PROPAGATES --
  it spreads from a victim to others by water, by air, by contact. It is not a poison
  that stops at the one who took it.

THE CRUELTY (what makes it deadly)
  The Strain feeds on the cure. VITALIS poured into a sufferer -- a healer's Restoration,
  a priest's mercy, a healing draught or spell -- does NOT fight it. It accelerates it.
  MECHANICALLY: any VITALIS / Restoration healing applied to an infected creature advances
  the infection one stage instead of helping. The kinder the hand, the faster the rot.
  (This is why Hemming's healers collapsed; it is why Danica's cure worked only because
  she poured her own life-force in directly rather than casting Restoration -- a gap the
  Strain's next version is being redesigned to close.)
  GM: a healer who does not know this will kill the patient trying to save them. Let that
  land hard the first time. Knowing it -- which the Codex teaches -- is the cure-lead.

THE KEEPER'S STAY (the antidote the Codex plants)
  The Forelhost family's own emergency counter, recorded in a Codex margin. It does not
  heal -- it STARVES the Strain of its binding and slows the body so the disease cannot
  propagate faster than the flesh sheds it.
  BUILT: GRAVITAS-heavy, NO VITALIS, designed against the Tears -- bind nothing, slow
  everything. A practitioner with the Codex (or who reasons it from the Doctrine) and a
  strong GRAVITAS source can brew it.
  EFFECT: arrests the Strain in a living body -- the infection stops advancing while the
  Stay holds. It is a STAY, not a cure: it buys time for a strong body to throw the disease
  off on its own (GM: a daily Might roll while stayed for the robust, or simply narrative
  time; the frail still need more). It will not save the already-dying.
  COUNTERPLAY: the Stay is the party's real lead toward saving Windhelm, toward anyone
  Davinia or Orion infect, and toward Danica if she is ever asked to cure this again.
  Whoever learns alchemy from the Codex can make it. Reward that.

DENYING IT AT THE SOURCE
  The Tears of Rahgot are the binding agent; nothing else propagates the Strain. Taking or
  destroying the Tears at Forelhost cripples Antoine's ability to make more (the party may
  not register they are making this choice -- see the Forelhost runsheet).

THE TEARS OF RAHGOT -- MECHANICAL RESOLUTION (why VITALIS accelerates instead of collapsing)
  A live tension in the existing rules: the Law of Opposition says a Primary VITALIS meeting
  a Primary VENITAS in a compound should simply COLLAPSE (Primary Negation) -- yet the Strain
  is explicitly fed, not cancelled, by VITALIS/Restoration. Those two established facts don't
  reconcile under the normal Law. This is not a contradiction to quietly ignore; it is the
  Tears' actual function.
  [LEGENDARY] Tears of Rahgot: VENITAS[P], ANIMA[S], CAECITAS[T], [SPECIAL: The Binding]
  THE BINDING inverts the Law of Opposition for this compound only -- rather than letting
  incoming VITALIS oppose and cancel the VENITAS normally, the Tears bind the two together,
  so a healer's Restoration feeds the rot instead of fighting it. No plant carries this
  property and no amount of Doctrine study derives it -- the Doctrine's own law says it
  cannot be done. Knowing the Tears break the rule requires the Codex itself (or equivalent
  in-world discovery); this is precisely why a player attempting to reverse-engineer the
  Strain cold, from alchemical theory alone, is working against something the theory says is
  impossible. This is also why the Keeper's Stay works as a counter and healing doesn't: the
  Stay is GRAVITAS-heavy with NO VITALIS, starving the Tears' binding mechanism rather than
  feeding it.

THE FULL FORMULA (reconstruction, verified against the current ingredient catalogue --
  Section 4/Additional Catalogue above; GM reference only, not something a Novice or even
  most Adepts could derive or execute)

  11 distinct ingredients, 21 total items in the pot -- 55 opposition pairs to audit. This
  is what "near-impossible to work out cold" means mechanically, not just narratively.

  Ingredient          Copies   Essences
  Nightshade          4        VENITAS[P] (pure)
  Deathbell           3        VENITAS[P], GRAVITAS[S]
  Nirnroot            3        CAECITAS[P], VENITAS[S], FULGUR[T]
  Skeever Tail        2        VENITAS[P], AGILITAS[T]
  Chokeberry          2        VENITAS[P], GRAVITAS[S], CAECITAS[T]
  Falmer Ear          2        CAECITAS[P], VENITAS[S], GRAVITAS[T]
  Human Heart         1        ANIMA[P], VENITAS[S], FORTITAS[T]
  Hagraven Feather    1        ANIMA[P], VENITAS[S], CAECITAS[T]
  Vampire Dust        1        ANIMA[P], CAECITAS[S], VITALIS[T]
  Bone Meal           1        VENITAS[P], GRAVITAS[S], ANIMA[T]
  Tears of Rahgot     1        [LEGENDARY] VENITAS[P], ANIMA[S], CAECITAS[T], [SPECIAL: The Binding]

  THE OPPOSITION AUDIT (why it doesn't collapse):
  - VITALIS<->VENITAS: the only VITALIS anywhere in the pot is Vampire Dust's VITALIS[T] --
    against a wall of VENITAS[P], that's Tertiary Negation only. No Primary VITALIS exists
    in the brew, so no collapse. This is the knife's edge the whole compound balances on --
    one wrong ingredient with a Primary or Secondary VITALIS ruins everything.
  - GRAVITAS<->AGILITAS: the GRAVITAS[S] sources (Deathbell/Chokeberry/Bone Meal) vs Skeever
    Tail's AGILITAS[T] -- Secondary Negation. The stray AGILITAS gets crushed; irrelevant,
    since propagation is the Tears' job, not an Essence expressed by the base compound.
  - CAECITAS<->FULGUR: CAECITAS[P] (multiple sources) vs Nirnroot's own FULGUR[T] --
    Tertiary Negation, consistent with Nirnroot's known internal paradox (Section 4).
  - FORTITAS<->ANIMA: Human Heart's FORTITAS[T] vs the ANIMA[P] stack -- Tertiary Negation.
  - IGNIS<->GLACIES: neither present. No interaction.

  THE TRAP A LESSER ALCHEMIST FALLS INTO: Imp Stool is a common, obvious VENITAS[P] source
  -- but it carries VITALIS[S] (Section 4). Drop it into this formula and VITALIS[S] vs the
  VENITAS[P] wall produces Secondary Negation fighting the brew's own payload. Any
  journeyman poisoner reaches for Imp Stool by reflex. Antoine did not. That choice --
  knowing which common ingredient to leave OUT -- is as much the formula's signature as
  anything he put in.

HOW IT WAS CREATED (GM narrative account -- for adjudicating questions, not a scene to
  read aloud verbatim; deliver it in pieces if it ever surfaces in play)
  Antoine had two things no independent alchemist has ever had together: the family Codex
  (four thousand years of Forelhost annotation on the Doctrine, including the empirical
  record of what the Tears of Rahgot actually do -- knowledge no Doctrine-trained
  practitioner outside the bloodline possesses) and the Tears themselves, a [LEGENDARY]
  reagent that breaks the Law of Opposition by design rather than accident.
  The formula above was NOT his first attempt. The Codex's own margins (Ismara's source
  material) record generations of Forelhost alchemists testing VENITAS compounds against
  the Tears before Antoine's work -- most of them either too weak to propagate reliably, or
  unstable enough to burn out in their own host before spreading. Antoine's contribution
  was the CONCENTRATION discipline this document's new mechanic describes: using precise
  copy-ratios (Nightshade at 4, tapering down to the Tears themselves at exactly 1) to
  force a compound where VENITAS dominates completely, every possible VITALIS contamination
  is kept below Primary, and the Tears' Binding has nothing to compete against. Where his
  ancestors treated the Codex's ratios as suggestion, Antoine treated them as the actual
  mechanism -- the same discipline Ismara is only now, independently, beginning to
  rediscover in her own notes (see The Forelhost Codex -- Ismara's Extract). That
  parallel is not a coincidence: she is walking the same road he already walked, from the
  same source text, toward a use of it he'd consider a betrayal of everything he built.
  Deployment (sourced, Antoine's Journal 1): the finished Strain went into Riften via the
  mead vats. ~73% transmission, ~89% lethality untreated within 14 days, ~94% with
  Restoration applied -- the healer's hand making it worse being the whole design, not an
  accident of the recipe.


